===The penthouse===
[[File:The Phelan Building penthouse.jpg|thumb|287px|The penthouse as of April 2014]]

An unusual feature of the building is a small [[Penthouse apartment|penthouse]]. Originally adorned by a rooftop garden, it was used by James D. Phelan to entertain dignitaries. It has later served as a photography studio in the 1960s,<ref>{{Citation|last=Seidkin|first=Phyllis|title=High Life at O’Farrell and Market|publisher=The San Francisco Examiner, Pictorial Living|page=10|date=August 25, 1963}}</ref> and was abandoned some time in the 1980s.

